<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="https://2.bp.blogspot.com/-DcQWvy0mNIE/WHuhJXG5ogI/AAAAAAAALfY/hMlvMwwrGGgu5UpwBwmFYVP5XFPsRc-pgCLcB/s1600/AP1150023.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="clear: left; float: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="474" src="https://2.bp.blogspot.com/-DcQWvy0mNIE/WHuhJXG5ogI/AAAAAAAALfY/hMlvMwwrGGgu5UpwBwmFYVP5XFPsRc-pgCLcB/s640/AP1150023.jpg" width="640" /></a></div><br /><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-P-uP-pLsVSg/WHuhLFo8BvI/AAAAAAAALfc/GJjhKS_MHskNhovTs_6p9XtOxamUQMB3QCLcB/s1600/AP1150013.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="clear: left; float: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="432" src="https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-P-uP-pLsVSg/WHuhLFo8BvI/AAAAAAAALfc/GJjhKS_MHskNhovTs_6p9XtOxamUQMB3QCLcB/s640/AP1150013.jpg" width="640" /></a></div>A return to wet and warmer weather for the second and final day of the <a href="http://www.expeditionguide.com/winterskillsweekend.php">Winter Skills Weekend</a>. Using mechanical assistance again we caught the Nevis Range gondola up onto Aonach Mor before wandering along through slushy snow and heather to the foot of the Nid ridge. Before leaving the house this morning we'd invested a bit of time learning about what contributes to instability in a snow pack as well talking about how we might plan a safe route of travel up our chosen mountain. Once up and into the snow proper we where able to take a practical look at things as there were in reality in a snow pack that actually behaved itself very well for my rutschblock and hand shear test demonstrations. With a damp morning turning into a wet afternoon we were back on the move again, following the ridge up and above the ski area to make a circuit of our little outing. <br /><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="https://4.bp.blogspot.com/-N2WXp5reYak/WHuhMQPtMrI/AAAAA